body_html:
@captify-alazorenko It sounds like there's some problem with your installation. How exactly did you install from sources?

Perhaps you can try this:

$ python
Python 2.7.12 (default, Nov 19 2016, 06:48:10) 
[GCC 5.4.0 20160609] on linux2
Type "help", "copyright", "credits" or "license" for more information.
>>> import tensorflow
>>> tensorflow
<module 'tensorflow' from '/usr/local/lib/python2.7/dist-packages/tensorflow/__init__.pyc'>
>>> quit()
$ ls /usr/local/lib/python2.7/dist-packages/tensorflow 
__init__.py   contrib  examples  python       tools
__init__.pyc  core     include   tensorboard

The idea is to figure out where your tensorflow installation is, and see whether it makes sense. You might be able to debug more depending on what you find there.

body:
@captify-alazorenko It sounds like there's some problem with your installation.  How exactly did you install from sources?

Perhaps you can try this:
```
$ python
Python 2.7.12 (default, Nov 19 2016, 06:48:10) 
[GCC 5.4.0 20160609] on linux2
Type "help", "copyright", "credits" or "license" for more information.
>>> import tensorflow
>>> tensorflow
<module 'tensorflow' from '/usr/local/lib/python2.7/dist-packages/tensorflow/__init__.pyc'>
>>> quit()
$ ls /usr/local/lib/python2.7/dist-packages/tensorflow 
__init__.py   contrib  examples  python       tools
__init__.pyc  core     include   tensorboard
```

The idea is to figure out where your tensorflow installation is, and see whether it makes sense.  You might be able to debug more depending on what you find there.
